                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.90H/40: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-12T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 12, 1938—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Personal for Engert from Murray. Your 131, December 27, 11 a.m. Since it now
                    seems impracticable for me to make my proposed trip to the Near East this
                    spring, I would suggest that you merely mention to the new Afghan Ambassador
                    that you hope to be able to visit Afghanistan sometime this year. Letter
                    follows. [Murray.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
